5|$|In 1153, {{the wife}} of Roger de Beaumont, 2ndEarl of Warwick, was tricked into believing {{that her husband was}} dead, and {{surrendered}} control of the castle to the invading army of Henry of Anjou, later King Henry II. According to the Gesta Regis Stephani, a 12th-century historical text, Roger de Beaumont died on hearing the news <b>that</b> <b>his</b> <b>wife</b> <b>had</b> handed over the castle. Henry later returned the castle to the Earls of Warwick as they had been supporters of his mother, Empress Matilda, in The Anarchy of 1135–1154.|$|E
